<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>beat a dead horse • work off the dead horse</xh5><p> <i>beat a dead horse</i>—(also: flog a dead horse) pursue a futile goal; try to revive interest in a dead issue: Son, we talked about this and the decision was “no.” You are <u>beating a dead horse</u>. </p><p><i>work off the dead horse</i>—(also: work out the dead horse) do work for which payment has already been made: The sailor was advanced one month’s pay.... During the first month out, he was “<u>working off the dead horse</u>.”</p> </entry>
